# IMP-0002

# Embedded Service Architecture

Status: Draft

Version: 0.1

Depends on:

* RFC-0020 Hypervisor Architecture
* RFC-0021 Hypervisor Scheduling Engine
* RFC-0025 Endpoint Advertisement
* IMP-0001 Repository Layout

---

# 1. Purpose

The AiDN Hypervisor SHALL operate as a self-contained network node.

Every installation SHALL be capable of participating in the AiDN network without requiring additional mandatory services.

Optional network services execute as embedded modules inside the Hypervisor process.

---

# 2. Design Principles

### ESA-1

The Hypervisor is the primary executable.

All other functionality is optional.

---

### ESA-2

Every embedded service MAY be enabled or disabled independently.

---

### ESA-3

Embedded services communicate through internal interfaces.

They SHALL NOT communicate over HTTP or gRPC when running inside the same process.

---

### ESA-4

Every embedded service MAY later be extracted into an independent process without changing its public interface.

---

# 3. Embedded Services

The Hypervisor MAY host the following services.

```text id="lm6ewi"
Hypervisor

├── Endpoint Manager

├── Scheduler

├── Runtime Manager

├── Resource Manager

├── Registry Client

├── Wallet

├── Validator

├── Advertisement Publisher

├── Metrics

└── Event Bus
```

All services execute within the same process unless explicitly configured otherwise.

---

# 4. Default Installation

A default installation SHALL require only one executable.

```text id="v6mnv3"
aidn-hypervisor
```

No external Registry, Wallet or Validator process is required.

---

# 5. Service Configuration

Example configuration:

```yaml id="w3zsv6"
services:

  wallet:
    enabled: true

  validator:
    enabled: false

  advertisement:
    enabled: true

  metrics:
    enabled: true
```

Services not listed SHALL use default values.

---

# 6. Service Lifecycle

Every embedded service follows the same lifecycle.

```text id="pqhl3j"
Registered

↓

Initialized

↓

Started

↓

Running

↓

Stopping

↓

Stopped
```

Services SHALL be started in dependency order.

Services SHALL be stopped in reverse dependency order.

---

# 7. Internal Communication

Embedded services SHALL communicate exclusively through internal interfaces.

Examples:

* Go interfaces
* Internal Event Bus
* Shared immutable domain objects

Direct REST or gRPC communication between embedded services is prohibited.

---

# 8. Event Bus

The Hypervisor SHALL expose an internal Event Bus.

Examples of published events include:

* EndpointCreated
* EndpointUpdated
* EndpointRemoved
* BundleInstalled
* BundleRemoved
* TaskStarted
* TaskCompleted
* ValidationCompleted
* AdvertisementPublished
* WalletUsageRecorded

Services SHALL subscribe only to events relevant to their responsibilities.

---

# 9. Service Independence

Each embedded service SHALL own its own internal state.

Direct access to another service's private state is prohibited.

Communication SHALL occur through:

* public interfaces;
* published events.

---

# 10. Optional Extraction

Any embedded service MAY later execute as an external process.

Extraction SHALL NOT require changes to:

* Scheduler;
* Endpoint Manager;
* Bundle Manager;
* Runtime Manager.

Only the transport implementation MAY change.

---

# 11. Resource Ownership

The Hypervisor Core owns all process resources.

Embedded services SHALL request resources through the Hypervisor Core.

Embedded services SHALL NOT allocate GPU, RAM or execution resources independently.

---

# 12. Failure Isolation

Failure of an embedded service SHALL NOT terminate the Hypervisor.

The Hypervisor SHALL:

* isolate the failure;
* record diagnostics;
* restart the service when appropriate;
* continue operating whenever possible.

Only unrecoverable Hypervisor Core failures MAY terminate the process.

---

# 13. Design Invariants

Invariant 1

One executable is sufficient to operate an AiDN node.

---

Invariant 2

All embedded services are optional.

---

Invariant 3

Internal communication never uses network protocols.

---

Invariant 4

Service extraction SHALL preserve interfaces.

---

Invariant 5

The Hypervisor Core remains the sole owner of execution resources.

---

Invariant 6

Every embedded service SHALL support three execution modes:

* Embedded
* External
* Mock

The service interface SHALL remain identical in all three modes.
